WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.000
I was at Warwick Castle in England when I met a stranger.

00:10.000 --> 00:19.000
He told me many stories about the past. I liked them very much.

00:19.000 --> 00:26.000
Then we saw some very old armour. There was a bullet hole in the armour.

00:26.000 --> 00:39.000
This hole is later. It comes after the invention of firearms, said the guide.

00:39.000 --> 00:47.000
I did it, said the stranger and smiled. I was very surprised.

00:47.000 --> 00:55.000
The stranger was staying at my hotel. He came to my room and gave me a matter of time.

00:55.000 --> 01:07.000
He gave me a manuscript. His name was Hank Morgan. This is his story.

01:07.000 --> 01:16.000
I was in my factory in Connecticut. A worker hit me on the head and I fell down.

01:16.000 --> 01:23.000
I woke up under a tree and saw a strange man in armour on a horse.

01:23.000 --> 01:32.000
He said I was his prisoner. His name was Sir Kay. I went with him to a village.

01:32.000 --> 01:43.000
He said it was Camelot. I was sure it was a lunatic asylum. I thought all the people were mad.

01:43.000 --> 01:51.000
They all looked at my clothes. They thought I was strange.

01:51.000 --> 01:58.000
I started to talk to a page. His name was Clarence.

01:58.000 --> 02:02.000
Where am I? I asked.

02:02.000 --> 02:08.000
King Arthur's court in the year 513, he answered.

02:08.000 --> 02:17.000
You are a prisoner. They are going to kill you. But I will come and visit you in prison.

02:17.000 --> 02:23.000
Then some people took me to the king at his round table.

02:23.000 --> 02:28.000
There were lots of knights sitting round the table eating.

02:28.000 --> 02:35.000
Lots of people served them food. Beautiful ladies watched from a balcony.

02:35.000 --> 02:44.000
Musicians played on another balcony. The room was very big and made of stone.

02:44.000 --> 02:49.000
The knights and ladies clothes were beautiful.

02:49.000 --> 02:57.000
An old man stood up and told a story. Everyone was bored and fell asleep.

02:57.000 --> 03:01.000
The old man was Merlin.

03:01.000 --> 03:11.000
Then Sir Kay told the story of my capture. He told a lot of lies and said I was very dangerous.

03:11.000 --> 03:19.000
He presented me to Queen Guinevere. He said my clothes were magic.

03:19.000 --> 03:30.000
They took away my clothes and then put me in prison. I fell asleep.

03:30.000 --> 03:38.000
When I woke up, I thought it was all a dream. Then I realized it was true.

03:38.000 --> 03:46.000
I was a prisoner at King Arthur's court. Clarence came to visit me.

03:46.000 --> 03:50.000
Help me to escape, I said to him.

03:50.000 --> 03:59.000
I can't, he answered. There are lots of guards and Merlin has put a spell on this prison.

03:59.000 --> 04:07.000
No one can escape. Tomorrow at noon, they are going to burn you.

04:07.000 --> 04:13.000
I was very miserable, but I had an idea.

04:13.000 --> 04:21.000
I am not afraid, I said. I am a very powerful magician.

04:21.000 --> 04:28.000
Is today the 20th of June? Yes, it is, said Clarence.

04:28.000 --> 04:37.000
Then go and tell the king that if he burns me, tomorrow the world will end in darkness.

04:37.000 --> 04:44.000
I'll end in light and warmth. Everyone will die.

04:44.000 --> 04:55.000
I knew from my studies that on the 21st of June, 513, there was a total solar eclipse.

04:55.000 --> 05:02.000
That was my magic to make the sun disappear.

05:02.000 --> 05:08.000
The next day they came to get me and tied me to a big tree.

05:08.000 --> 05:15.000
People sat to watch all around. Everyone wanted to see.

05:15.000 --> 05:24.000
I was afraid. And if my calculations were wrong, then everyone looked up.

05:24.000 --> 05:28.000
The eclipse was beginning.

05:28.000 --> 05:33.000
Ban him! Shouted Merlin.

05:33.000 --> 05:40.000
Stop! Shouted King Arthur. Have mercy!

05:40.000 --> 05:49.000
Do not destroy the sun. What do you want? I can give you anything.

05:49.000 --> 05:55.000
I said I wanted to be his minister and help him. And he agreed.

05:55.000 --> 06:02.000
The solar eclipse was now total. Everything was dark.

06:02.000 --> 06:11.000
So I pointed to the sun and shouted, pass away and do not harm us.

06:11.000 --> 06:18.000
The sun started to come out again and everyone was happy.

06:18.000 --> 06:25.000
I became the first minister and the most powerful man in Camelot.

06:25.000 --> 06:29.000
Clarence was my assistant.

06:29.000 --> 06:37.000
I had beautiful but very uncomfortable clothes and the best rooms after the king.

06:37.000 --> 06:41.000
People came from all over the country to see me.

06:41.000 --> 06:50.000
I was famous. But they wanted another piece of powerful magic from me.

06:50.000 --> 07:03.000
Merlin was in prison. He was my enemy. So I said I wanted to explode his tower with fire from the sky.

07:03.000 --> 07:09.000
His tower was an old Roman one and very solid.

07:09.000 --> 07:17.000
One stormy night I filled it with gunpowder and attached a metal stick to it.

07:17.000 --> 07:26.000
Then I told everyone to gather and we watched as the lightning hit the tower and it exploded.

07:26.000 --> 07:34.000
Everyone was afraid. They thought I was a very powerful magician.

07:34.000 --> 07:40.000
As time passed I realized that the people in Camelot were like children.

07:40.000 --> 07:48.000
They were very simple. They couldn't read or write and they were not logical.

07:48.000 --> 07:52.000
They believed everything they heard.

07:52.000 --> 07:58.000
I started to open secret schools and a secret military academy.

07:58.000 --> 08:02.000
I put down telephone wires to have telephones.

08:02.000 --> 08:06.000
I wanted to create newspapers.

08:06.000 --> 08:09.000
I taught Clarence to be a journalist.

08:09.000 --> 08:18.000
The king and the nobles believed they were better than me because I was not noble but they respected my intelligence.

08:18.000 --> 08:25.000
I thought I was better than them because I was intelligent but I liked them.

08:25.000 --> 08:32.000
No one admitted all this and we got on very well.

08:32.000 --> 08:38.000
After four years King Arthur was very happy with my work.

08:38.000 --> 08:42.000
He was richer because I managed his money well.

08:42.000 --> 08:48.000
I also distributed it better and the people of Camelot were happier.

08:48.000 --> 08:52.000
They started to call me the boss.

08:52.000 --> 08:55.000
I liked it.

08:55.000 --> 09:00.000
The main entertainment at Camelot was jousting.

09:00.000 --> 09:05.000
Hundreds of knights took part and many were injured.

09:05.000 --> 09:10.000
Sometimes the knights went to save princesses from dragons.

09:10.000 --> 09:15.000
They believed in dragons and giants.

09:15.000 --> 09:19.000
One day a girl came to Camelot.

09:19.000 --> 09:23.000
Her name was Alyson de la Catilwas.

09:23.000 --> 09:32.000
She said her mistress and 44 girls, many of whom were princesses, were captive in a castle.

09:32.000 --> 09:39.000
The guards were three huge men with four arms and one eye.

09:39.000 --> 09:44.000
At Camelot they decided I had to rescue them.

09:44.000 --> 09:50.000
I decided it was time for a holiday so I agreed.

09:50.000 --> 09:54.000
I asked Alyson the questions.

09:54.000 --> 09:57.000
She couldn't tell me anything.

09:57.000 --> 10:00.000
Where is the castle?

10:00.000 --> 10:04.000
Many miles away she answered.

10:04.000 --> 10:07.000
How many? I asked.

10:07.000 --> 10:13.000
I don't know. She said they all look the same.

10:13.000 --> 10:17.000
I got up early and had breakfast.

10:17.000 --> 10:20.000
Then I put on my armour.

10:20.000 --> 10:23.000
It took a very long time.

10:23.000 --> 10:28.000
There were many pieces and I couldn't move or do anything.

10:28.000 --> 10:33.000
They had to carry me out and lift me onto the horse.

10:33.000 --> 10:37.000
I felt like a ship going to sea.

10:37.000 --> 10:41.000
Then Alyson climbed onto the horse behind me.

10:41.000 --> 10:45.000
She had to show me the way to the castle.

10:45.000 --> 10:54.000
We started out and everyone waved goodbye to us.

10:54.000 --> 10:57.000
Chapter 2

10:57.000 --> 11:00.000
Free men

11:00.000 --> 11:03.000
We were immediately in the countryside.

11:03.000 --> 11:07.000
It was lovely and pleasant, very green.

11:07.000 --> 11:11.000
There were a lot of trees, fields and rivers.

11:11.000 --> 11:14.000
Then it started to get hot.

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
Sweat ran into my eyes.

11:16.000 --> 11:20.000
My armour got heavier and heavier.

11:20.000 --> 11:29.000
Finally, Alyson took off my helmet, filled it with water and poured it into my armour.

11:29.000 --> 11:31.000
I felt better.

11:31.000 --> 11:35.000
Alyson never stopped talking.

11:35.000 --> 11:41.000
I told her to take a rest but not use up all the air.

11:41.000 --> 11:43.000
Night approached.

11:43.000 --> 11:46.000
It got dark fast.

11:46.000 --> 11:51.000
I found a place for Alyson to sleep and then one for me.

11:51.000 --> 11:57.000
It got very cold and lots of insects climbed inside my armour.

11:57.000 --> 12:00.000
I couldn't sleep.

12:00.000 --> 12:05.000
In the morning I was cold, tired and hungry.

12:05.000 --> 12:10.000
Sandy was bright and fresh.

12:14.000 --> 12:17.000
We set off.

12:17.000 --> 12:22.000
Suddenly we met a group of poor, ragged people.

12:22.000 --> 12:27.000
I had breakfast with them and saw they were very happy.

12:27.000 --> 12:30.000
They were free men.

12:30.000 --> 12:37.000
They were farmers and artisans, about seven-tenths of the population.

12:37.000 --> 12:46.000
They were the only useful part of the population, but they could do nothing without the permission of their lords or the church.

12:46.000 --> 12:50.000
They couldn't sell anything without paying tax.

12:51.000 --> 12:58.000
They had to give part of their produce to the lords and bishops and work for them.

12:58.000 --> 13:05.000
These men were free, but they were repairing the bishops' roads as part of their duty.

13:05.000 --> 13:13.000
I asked them, if you had a vote tomorrow, would you vote for a king?

13:13.000 --> 13:18.000
They didn't understand, except for one man.

13:18.000 --> 13:25.000
He said, in a nation with a vote, there are no kings or bishops.

13:25.000 --> 13:35.000
I decided to send him to my man factory, a school where Clarence was teaching people to read and write.

13:35.000 --> 13:40.000
I gave the men three pennies for my breakfast.

13:40.000 --> 13:44.000
It was a lot of money, but they deserved it.

13:44.000 --> 13:47.000
Then I lit my pipe.

13:47.000 --> 13:52.000
The next day we were crossing a meadow when Sandy shouted,

13:52.000 --> 13:56.000
Defend yourself danger!

13:56.000 --> 14:01.000
Six armed knights were in the shade of a tree.

14:01.000 --> 14:03.000
They attacked me.

14:03.000 --> 14:06.000
I lit my pipe.

14:06.000 --> 14:09.000
They suddenly stopped.

14:09.000 --> 14:13.000
Sandy said they thought I was a dragon.

14:13.000 --> 14:25.000
Then she told them to go to King Arthur's court and surrender, becoming my knights.

14:25.000 --> 14:29.000
Sandy told me the story of the knights.

14:29.000 --> 14:31.000
It was very long.

14:31.000 --> 14:38.000
While she was speaking, I remembered the girl I loved in Connecticut, and I was sad.

14:39.000 --> 14:43.000
But then we saw a big castle.

14:43.000 --> 14:47.000
Outside the castle I met one of my knights.

14:47.000 --> 14:50.000
He was my soap missionary.

14:50.000 --> 14:55.000
He went about selling soap because I wanted a cleaner country.

14:55.000 --> 15:02.000
He didn't manage to sell soap in that castle because someone died while they were using it.

15:02.000 --> 15:08.000
He told me the owner was Morgan Le Fay, King Arthur's sister.

15:08.000 --> 15:12.000
Her husband was King Urien's.

15:12.000 --> 15:19.000
Their kingdom was so small you could stand in the middle of it and throw a brick into the next kingdom.

15:19.000 --> 15:27.000
Morgan Le Fay had a terrible reputation, but at first she seemed very kind.

15:27.000 --> 15:30.000
She invited us to have dinner.

15:30.000 --> 15:36.000
Then a page touched her, and she stabbed him.

15:36.000 --> 15:39.000
She was very bad.

15:39.000 --> 15:46.000
Sandy told her I was the boss, and she was very frightened of me.

15:46.000 --> 15:52.000
I heard a terrible sound and asked to see where it came from.

15:52.000 --> 15:58.000
As I entered the cell, I saw something I would never forget.

15:58.000 --> 16:03.000
A young giant of a man was stretched on a rack.

16:03.000 --> 16:08.000
A poor young woman with a baby was in a corner.

16:08.000 --> 16:13.000
The man had killed a deer, a terrible crime.

16:13.000 --> 16:18.000
I told Morgan to free him and leave me with the family.

16:18.000 --> 16:27.000
The wife wanted the man to confess, then Morgan would execute him quickly and stop his suffering.

16:27.000 --> 16:37.000
The man refused because the confession would give Morgan the right to take away all property from his wife and leave her with nothing.

16:37.000 --> 16:45.000
I thought, this is a real man, a heart of gold.

16:45.000 --> 16:48.000
I asked to see her prisoners.

16:48.000 --> 16:51.000
It was terrible.

16:51.000 --> 16:54.000
Some were there so long they had gone mad.

16:54.000 --> 17:03.000
A young bride and her husband, separated by their lord on their wedding night, now didn't recognize each other.

17:03.000 --> 17:07.000
Morgan Lafe didn't even know who some of them were.

17:07.000 --> 17:11.000
An old man in his cell could see his home.

17:11.000 --> 17:15.000
He had a wife and five children.

17:15.000 --> 17:24.000
Over the years, he had seen five funerals, but he didn't know which member of his family was still alive.

17:24.000 --> 17:29.000
I set all Morgan's prisoners free except for one noble.

17:29.000 --> 17:33.000
I didn't care about him.

17:33.000 --> 17:38.000
The next morning I was very happy to leave the castle.

17:38.000 --> 17:42.000
Sandy kept telling me stories.

17:42.000 --> 17:45.000
I met with my toothbrush missionary.

17:45.000 --> 17:50.000
He was very angry with my stove polish missionary.

17:50.000 --> 18:00.000
Of course there were no stoves yet, but I wanted to prepare people for them and teach them about keeping a tidy home.

18:00.000 --> 18:08.000
We had another chance meeting with the old man who had watched the funerals from Morgan's prison.

18:08.000 --> 18:11.000
He was with his whole family now.

18:11.000 --> 18:17.000
The funerals had been false, a torture invented by Morgan.

18:17.000 --> 18:20.000
I was happy for him.

18:20.000 --> 18:26.000
Suddenly Sandy said, the castle, look!

18:26.000 --> 18:33.000
It isn't a castle, it's a big sty. I said to Sandy.

18:33.000 --> 18:39.000
It wasn't enchanted before, she said.

18:39.000 --> 18:48.000
Sandy really believed she saw a castle with monster guards and captive princesses inside.

18:48.000 --> 18:56.000
So I paid the men who guarded the pigs to go away and rescued the ladies.

18:56.000 --> 19:04.000
Sandy embraced the pigs, believing they were princesses.

19:04.000 --> 19:08.000
The next day we met some pilgrims on the road.

19:08.000 --> 19:16.000
They were going to the valley of holiness, a place with a miraculous stream of water.

19:16.000 --> 19:22.000
Suddenly we saw a terrible sight, a group of slaves.

19:22.000 --> 19:28.000
The clothes were dirty and torn, their faces were grey.

19:28.000 --> 19:36.000
They were injured from the chains, a girl fell and the guards hit her.

19:36.000 --> 19:42.000
Then her new owner arrived to take her baby and her away.

19:42.000 --> 19:50.000
She cried, and a man tried to embrace her. It was her husband.

19:50.000 --> 19:57.000
They were separated. They would never see each other again.

19:57.000 --> 20:06.000
I still feel terrible when I think about that scene today. I will never forget it.

20:06.000 --> 20:14.000
We arrived at a pub where I met a night I knew. He was my stovepipe hat missionary.

20:14.000 --> 20:18.000
He wore armour with a hat instead of a helmet.

20:18.000 --> 20:25.000
He said there was a terrible problem in the valley of holiness. The water had stopped.

20:25.000 --> 20:32.000
Merlin was there now. He was trying to make the water come back with magic.

20:32.000 --> 20:44.000
I sent a message to Clarence. Send me pipes, extensions and two trained assistants.

20:44.000 --> 20:50.000
Chapter 3. The Holy Fountain

20:50.000 --> 20:57.000
We traveled quickly with the pilgrims and arrived in the valley of holiness before sunset.

20:57.000 --> 21:02.000
All the people there were sad. I met the abbot.

21:02.000 --> 21:11.000
Hurry my son, he said. Save our valley, or we will lose 200 years of work.

21:11.000 --> 21:15.000
But do not use the devil's magic.

21:15.000 --> 21:21.000
I only use God's work, I said. But what about Merlin?

21:21.000 --> 21:29.000
He promised too, but please try immediately answered the abbot.

21:29.000 --> 21:37.000
I can't, I said. It is not fair. I must wait until Merlin stops.

21:37.000 --> 21:45.000
I asked to see the well. I made an inspection and realized that the well probably had a leak.

21:45.000 --> 21:50.000
I went down the well and saw there was a big hole at the bottom.

21:50.000 --> 21:57.000
That was the problem, but I had to wait for Merlin to stop.

21:57.000 --> 22:01.000
The next day I decided to visit some hermits.

22:01.000 --> 22:11.000
They were all very dirty and very strange. One had chains. One was naked and black with dirt.

22:11.000 --> 22:16.000
One stood on a pillar and moved up and down.

22:16.000 --> 22:25.000
Eventually I attached a sewing machine to him and made shirts. It made a lot of money.

22:26.000 --> 22:34.000
Soon Merlin decided to give in. So with my assistance I repaired the well and put in a pump.

22:34.000 --> 22:39.000
Then we made a tunnel for the water to flow outside too.

22:39.000 --> 22:46.000
I put down some fireworks. I called everyone and started the miracle.

22:46.000 --> 22:52.000
I said very big, strange, invented words.

22:52.000 --> 23:01.000
Everyone thought they were magic. Then I lit the fireworks and the water started to flow.

23:01.000 --> 23:06.000
It was a huge miracle.

23:06.000 --> 23:12.000
Soon after I asked if the monks wanted a bath. They were horrified.

23:12.000 --> 23:19.000
Baths were forbidden because people having baths stopped the water in the past.

23:19.000 --> 23:24.000
But I told them it was a different problem that stopped the water, not the bath.

23:24.000 --> 23:33.000
They were very happy and loved the swimming pool I built for them to wash in.

23:33.000 --> 23:39.000
One day I was walking in the valley when I heard a voice in a cave.

23:39.000 --> 23:43.000
It was one of my telephone operators.

23:43.000 --> 23:51.000
I asked to speak to Camelot and learnt that the king and the court were coming to visit the valley.

23:51.000 --> 24:01.000
When I returned to the monastery I had a horrible surprise, a new giant magician.

24:01.000 --> 24:10.000
He said he knew what everyone was doing, the Emperor of the East, the Supreme Lord of India and others.

24:10.000 --> 24:20.000
Everyone believed him and was very surprised. I asked, what is my right hand doing?

24:20.000 --> 24:29.000
He didn't know. He was very worried. No one had ever asked that sort of simple question before.

24:29.000 --> 24:34.000
Then I asked, what is the king doing?

24:34.000 --> 24:39.000
He answered, he is sleeping in the palace.

24:39.000 --> 24:50.000
Everyone was amazed, but I answered, he isn't. He is travelling by horse. He will be here in three days.

24:50.000 --> 25:00.000
No one believed me, but I checked every day with my telephone operators and when the king was arriving I announced this to the abbot.

25:00.000 --> 25:07.000
People immediately stopped believing the false magician and believed me again.

25:07.000 --> 25:24.000
It is not difficult to be a successful magician in King Arthur's time, but it is hard work and you can't rest.

25:24.000 --> 25:31.000
When the king arrived he told me about his new army. I was not happy.

25:31.000 --> 25:43.000
I had a military school and I wanted to make my students officers, but when we had an examination of the candidates the nobles did not accept my men.

25:43.000 --> 25:54.000
They only accepted other nobles who were stupid and ignorant. My men were very well prepared, but they were not noble.

25:54.000 --> 26:00.000
Another problem with these people and their strange ideas.

26:00.000 --> 26:08.000
I had another idea, a new regiment consisting only of nobles to keep them happy.

26:08.000 --> 26:16.000
And then the rest of the army made up of my soldiers, the real army. Everyone was happy.

26:16.000 --> 26:22.000
I decided to go on a trip through the kingdom to see the general conditions.

26:22.000 --> 26:33.000
The king wanted to come too and told me to wait. He had to do his ceremony. He touched the sick and cured them.

26:33.000 --> 26:41.000
Often it worked. People were convinced his touch was magic and their belief made them better.

26:41.000 --> 26:45.000
The king did his best. He was a good man.

26:45.000 --> 26:55.000
The ceremony was very long and I was bored. He touched every sick person and gave them a coin.

26:55.000 --> 27:04.000
I decided to stop the gold coins and make copper ones. This saved the kingdom a lot of money.

27:04.000 --> 27:11.000
During the touching ceremony I saw another of my innovations, a newspaper.

27:11.000 --> 27:23.000
I was very happy with the result. It wasn't perfect and I wanted to improve it, but it was good enough and everyone was amazed by it.

27:23.000 --> 27:29.000
I was as proud of it as a mother of her new baby.

27:29.000 --> 27:36.000
I suggested the king tell Queen Gweniver of our departure, but he was sad.

27:36.000 --> 27:44.000
When Solancelot is here, the queen doesn't notice if I arrive or depart, he said.

27:44.000 --> 27:55.000
I was sorry for him. I thought the queen was beautiful, but not very intelligent.

27:55.000 --> 28:03.000
Later that evening I helped the king to dress himself as a peasant, ready for our journey into his kingdom.

28:04.000 --> 28:15.000
I cut his hair short. Nobles had long hair cut short at the front and peasants had short hair and the slaves had long hair.

28:15.000 --> 28:22.000
I cut his hair like a peasant and gave him a long simple tunic.

28:22.000 --> 28:29.000
We left early in the morning. On the road some noble people passed.

28:29.000 --> 28:35.000
I had to tell the king to bow to them. He didn't know how to behave.

28:35.000 --> 28:40.000
He wasn't good at bowing and one of the nobles tried to hit him.

28:40.000 --> 28:44.000
I stepped in and he whipped me instead.

28:44.000 --> 28:51.000
Next we met two knights. The king did not move off the road.

28:51.000 --> 28:58.000
He didn't understand that peasants had no rights. He believed the knights would ride around him.

28:58.000 --> 29:06.000
They didn't. They insulted the king who answered. This made them furious.

29:06.000 --> 29:19.000
To save the situation I insulted them more. They turned and started to attack us, so I threw some dynamite at them and they exploded.

29:19.000 --> 29:25.000
The king thought it was magic. I told him I could not repeat it another time.

29:25.000 --> 29:32.000
He said, you must read my thoughts and stop me before I make mistakes.

29:32.000 --> 29:38.000
I can't, I answered. He was amazed.

29:38.000 --> 29:46.000
But Merlin can, he said. I realized I had made a mistake.

29:46.000 --> 29:56.000
I said, Merlin can see a few minutes into the future. I can see centuries into the future.

29:56.000 --> 30:07.000
I don't bother with small prophecy like Merlin. He was convinced.

30:07.000 --> 30:13.000
Chapter 4. The Yankee and the King

30:13.000 --> 30:22.000
On the morning of the fourth day, when the sun was coming up, I decided to drill the king.

30:22.000 --> 30:34.000
Sir, I said, you are too like a soldier, a lord. This is not good. You must try to look poor and miserable.

30:34.000 --> 30:43.000
The king tried to walk like a poor peasant, but he was not convincing. He had too much spirit.

30:43.000 --> 30:50.000
I said to him, what will you say when we ask for hospitality in a house?

30:50.000 --> 30:55.000
Violet, give me what you have answered the king.

30:55.000 --> 31:06.000
No, you cannot say, Violet, you are not a lord. I answered. You must say, brother.

31:06.000 --> 31:18.000
The king tried his best. Give me the sack, he said. I must try to stoop and await that are not honorable.

31:18.000 --> 31:25.000
He tried, but it was very difficult for him to stoop. I thought about work.

31:25.000 --> 31:31.000
I thought about the people who believe that a day of intellectual work is hard.

31:31.000 --> 31:43.000
They don't understand that work is physical. It is silly to pay higher wages to intellectuals than to people who work with their bodies.

31:43.000 --> 31:51.000
We saw a very small poor house in the distance. We arrived in the middle of the afternoon.

31:51.000 --> 31:59.000
There was no sign of life. Everything looked ruined and there was no living thing.

31:59.000 --> 32:04.000
We pushed the door open and saw some forms in the dark.

32:05.000 --> 32:07.000
One sat up.

32:07.000 --> 32:09.000
Have mercy!

32:09.000 --> 32:17.000
cried a woman. They have taken everything. There is nothing here.

32:17.000 --> 32:22.000
I do not want anything, poor woman, I said.

32:22.000 --> 32:28.000
Then you are not a priest or a lord? She asked.

32:28.000 --> 32:40.000
No. I am a stranger, I replied. Let me come in and help you. You are sick and in trouble, I said.

32:40.000 --> 32:52.000
Go away, she said. We are in trouble with the lord and the church, and we have the small box. You must go away.

32:52.000 --> 32:58.000
I told the king to go away, but he refused.

32:58.000 --> 33:11.000
The king does not know fear and has no trouble with the church. I must stay and help. It is the duty of a night, he said.

33:11.000 --> 33:14.000
We gave the woman water.

33:14.000 --> 33:21.000
Please go out that ladder and tell me what you see, said the woman.

33:21.000 --> 33:26.000
The king went up the ladder which led to another part of the little hut.

33:26.000 --> 33:30.000
On his way, he noticed a man.

33:30.000 --> 33:35.000
Is that your husband sleeping? He asked.

33:35.000 --> 33:45.000
No. He died three hours ago. Now he is at peace, said the woman.

33:45.000 --> 33:54.000
The king climbed the ladder and came back with a poor girl of fifteen. She was dying.

33:54.000 --> 33:59.000
He said there was another girl who was already dead.

33:59.000 --> 34:05.000
He lay the girl next to the woman who sat with her until she died.

34:05.000 --> 34:10.000
I brought the other child to lie next to her.

34:10.000 --> 34:13.000
The woman told us her story.

34:13.000 --> 34:20.000
They were persecuted by the lord and the church who made them work and took all their property.

34:20.000 --> 34:28.000
They had nothing to eat, and their three sons were unjustly in prison for a theft they had not committed.

34:28.000 --> 34:31.000
Then they got smallpox.

34:31.000 --> 34:39.000
At midnight, they were all dead.

34:39.000 --> 34:43.000
We continued our journey and came to a small house.

34:43.000 --> 34:49.000
We asked for hospitality, and the couple who lived there was kind.

34:49.000 --> 34:56.000
I spoke to the man and discovered that he did not like the injustice of the country's laws.

34:56.000 --> 34:59.000
I liked him.

34:59.000 --> 35:06.000
We stayed for some days with the man whose name was Marco and his wife, Phyllis.

35:06.000 --> 35:11.000
I said the king was a farmer and I was his assistant.

35:11.000 --> 35:17.000
One day, I decided to have a special lunch at Marco's house.

35:17.000 --> 35:23.000
I invited a lot of people, all the craftsmen of the town.

35:23.000 --> 35:28.000
Marco was terrified by the cost, which was too much for him.

35:28.000 --> 35:31.000
I paid for everything.

35:31.000 --> 35:35.000
Everyone thought I was very rich.

35:36.000 --> 35:41.000
At the lunch, I tried to explain economics to the men.

35:41.000 --> 35:48.000
I told them that in my part of the country, people earned less, but everything cost less.

35:48.000 --> 35:53.000
So in my part of the country, people were better off.

35:53.000 --> 35:56.000
They couldn't understand.

35:56.000 --> 36:00.000
But we earned double what you earn. This is better.

36:00.000 --> 36:03.000
Insisted one man.

36:03.000 --> 36:07.000
But we pay less than half of what you pay.

36:07.000 --> 36:13.000
Therefore we have more money and can buy more things, I replied.

36:13.000 --> 36:21.000
They could not understand the idea which was new to them, and I could not explain it to them.

36:21.000 --> 36:24.000
I was very disappointed.

36:24.000 --> 36:27.000
So I tried another subject.

36:27.000 --> 36:30.000
I talked about crime and punishment.

36:30.000 --> 36:35.000
And I said they were committing crimes by earning more than was allowed by their lord.

36:35.000 --> 36:38.000
This was a mistake.

36:38.000 --> 36:43.000
I thought we could laugh about it, but they were terrified.

36:43.000 --> 36:49.000
They didn't know me, and they were worried that I wanted to report them.

36:49.000 --> 36:55.000
The king started talking about farming, but he knew nothing about it.

36:55.000 --> 36:59.000
The men started to say that he was mad.

36:59.000 --> 37:04.000
One wants to betray us, and the other is mad.

37:04.000 --> 37:09.000
They shouted.

37:09.000 --> 37:15.000
A fight started and the king was delighted, but I made him escape.

37:15.000 --> 37:17.000
We were in danger.

37:17.000 --> 37:24.000
We ran to the woods and hid in a tree, but the people found us and wanted to kill us.

37:25.000 --> 37:29.000
Luckily a noble arrived and saved us.

37:29.000 --> 37:34.000
He took us with him to a nearby town where he had business.

37:34.000 --> 37:38.000
Then we had another terrible surprise.

37:38.000 --> 37:43.000
He took us to the market and sold us as slaves.

37:43.000 --> 37:48.000
He sold the king for seven dollars and me for nine.

37:48.000 --> 37:50.000
I was offended.

37:50.000 --> 37:56.000
I was worth at least fifteen, and the king twelve.

37:56.000 --> 38:01.000
We were chained to the slaves by the master who was hard and cruel.

38:01.000 --> 38:06.000
We got lost in the snow, and five people died.

38:06.000 --> 38:12.000
Then a woman arrived screaming and tried to find protection with us.

38:12.000 --> 38:17.000
The people in her village said she was a witch and wanted to burn her.

38:17.000 --> 38:20.000
Our slave master helped them.

38:20.000 --> 38:23.000
We could not help her.

38:23.000 --> 38:31.000
Our master was angry about the dead slaves and revenged himself on this poor woman.

38:31.000 --> 38:34.000
Then we saw a procession.

38:34.000 --> 38:39.000
A young girl of eighteen was sitting on a coffin in a cart.

38:39.000 --> 38:41.000
She had a baby.

38:41.000 --> 38:46.000
With her was a priest who told her story.

38:46.000 --> 38:49.000
She was a young wife and mother.

38:49.000 --> 38:54.000
Then the army took her husband away to be a soldier.

38:54.000 --> 38:59.000
She had no work and was starving with her baby.

38:59.000 --> 39:03.000
So she stole a small piece of linen.

39:03.000 --> 39:06.000
The judge decided to hang her.

39:06.000 --> 39:12.000
The owner of the linen felt so bad he committed suicide.

39:12.000 --> 39:15.000
She cried and held her baby.

39:15.000 --> 39:22.000
But the priest who was very kind to her made a speech against the laws and the sentence

39:22.000 --> 39:26.000
and promised to look after the baby.

39:26.000 --> 39:34.000
There was gratitude in her face when she died.

39:34.000 --> 39:39.000
Chapter 5 War

39:39.000 --> 39:42.000
I had a plan to escape.

39:42.000 --> 39:49.000
I had to wait for many weeks, but in London my chance finally came.

39:49.000 --> 39:52.000
Immediately things went wrong.

39:52.000 --> 39:55.000
I couldn't get the king's chains off.

39:55.000 --> 39:59.000
The slave master interrupted me.

39:59.000 --> 40:03.000
When he went outside I followed him and attacked him in the dark.

40:03.000 --> 40:07.000
But the police arrested me and put me in jail.

40:07.000 --> 40:11.000
I said that I was a nobles servant.

40:11.000 --> 40:15.000
They were afraid of the nobles and let me go.

40:15.000 --> 40:21.000
Then I discovered that the other slaves had killed the slave master.

40:21.000 --> 40:26.000
They were all in prison, condemned to death.

40:26.000 --> 40:32.000
I found a telegraph station and sent a message to Clarence.

40:32.000 --> 40:35.000
Send knights to save the king and I.

40:35.000 --> 40:37.000
They want to hang us.

40:37.000 --> 40:40.000
Tomorrow.

40:40.000 --> 40:43.000
Everyone in London was looking for me.

40:43.000 --> 40:48.000
They took the slaves about London to recognize me.

40:48.000 --> 40:51.000
Unfortunately one of them saw me.

40:51.000 --> 40:56.000
They took me to the other slaves and decided to hang us that day.

40:56.000 --> 41:00.000
The knights would never arrive in time.

41:00.000 --> 41:03.000
It was too late.

41:03.000 --> 41:07.000
They took us to the execution place.

41:07.000 --> 41:12.000
The king tried to say who he was, but everyone laughed at him.

41:12.000 --> 41:16.000
They started to hang the slaves.

41:16.000 --> 41:20.000
Then they started to put the rope around the king's neck.

41:20.000 --> 41:22.000
It was dreadful.

41:22.000 --> 41:25.000
I couldn't move.

41:25.000 --> 41:29.000
Suddenly, a grand sight.

41:29.000 --> 41:35.000
Five hundred knights in armor on bicycles.

41:35.000 --> 41:40.000
Salonsalot and the knights saved the king.

41:40.000 --> 41:44.000
Clarence was very happy.

41:44.000 --> 41:46.000
What a surprise, eh?

41:46.000 --> 41:52.000
He said, the boys practiced for a long time.

41:52.000 --> 41:56.000
Soon I was home again in Camelot.

41:56.000 --> 41:59.000
I had to fight Sir Sagremor in a tournament.

41:59.000 --> 42:02.000
Everyone came to see it.

42:02.000 --> 42:06.000
The knights all supported Sir Sagremor.

42:06.000 --> 42:09.000
Merlin did some magic to protect him.

42:09.000 --> 42:15.000
I only had Clarence to support me.

42:15.000 --> 42:19.000
We started the fight.

42:19.000 --> 42:25.000
Sir Sagremor was in full armor, but I was wearing light clothes.

42:25.000 --> 42:30.000
Everyone thought I was ridiculous, but I could move fast and avoid him.

42:30.000 --> 42:33.000
He couldn't catch me.

42:33.000 --> 42:37.000
He got very angry and wanted to kill me.

42:37.000 --> 42:40.000
I used my lasso.

42:40.000 --> 42:45.000
They didn't know about cowboys and were amazed.

42:45.000 --> 42:50.000
I pulled Sir Sagremor off his horse and won the fight.

42:50.000 --> 42:56.000
But Merlin stole my lasso and Sir Sagremor wanted to fight again.

42:56.000 --> 42:59.000
I shot him with a gun.

42:59.000 --> 43:01.000
Everyone was shocked.

43:01.000 --> 43:03.000
They thought it was magic.

43:03.000 --> 43:05.000
The knights were angry.

43:05.000 --> 43:09.000
Five hundred of them attacked me all at once.

43:09.000 --> 43:14.000
I shot some and the others escaped.

43:14.000 --> 43:17.000
Everyone was afraid of me.

43:17.000 --> 43:21.000
For three years I improved the country.

43:21.000 --> 43:25.000
It was happy, civilized, with more money.

43:25.000 --> 43:28.000
Slavery was illegal.

43:28.000 --> 43:35.000
I wanted a republic, but decided to wait until King Arthur died.

43:35.000 --> 43:39.000
Then one day my child got sick.

43:39.000 --> 43:42.000
I was married to Sandy.

43:42.000 --> 43:45.000
I had married her because it was polite.

43:45.000 --> 43:48.000
But then I realized I loved her.

43:48.000 --> 43:52.000
I was totally happy with her.

43:52.000 --> 43:54.000
We had a daughter.

43:54.000 --> 43:57.000
Now she was sick.

43:57.000 --> 44:03.000
Celancelot, a very kind man, helped Sandy and I to look after her.

44:03.000 --> 44:11.000
Then we decided to take her to the sea for her health and sailed to France.

44:11.000 --> 44:15.000
When there was no news, I sailed back.

44:15.000 --> 44:18.000
Everything was a disaster.

44:18.000 --> 44:21.000
Clarence explained that the king was dead.

44:21.000 --> 44:23.000
Gweniver was a nun.

44:23.000 --> 44:29.000
The knights were fighting and the church wanted to dominate the land.

44:29.000 --> 44:31.000
We had to fight.

44:31.000 --> 44:34.000
It was time for the revolution.

44:34.000 --> 44:39.000
We declared a republic and the knights came to fight us.

44:39.000 --> 44:44.000
We hid in a cave and put dynamite everywhere.

44:44.000 --> 44:50.000
There were only fifty-four of us and twenty-five thousand of them.

44:50.000 --> 44:57.000
But when they attacked, we electrocuted them and then made them explode.

44:57.000 --> 45:01.000
We won.

45:01.000 --> 45:04.000
Postscript by Clarence.

45:04.000 --> 45:07.000
I must finish the story.

45:07.000 --> 45:10.000
The boss made a mistake.

45:10.000 --> 45:17.000
He wanted to offer help to some injured knights, but one of them recognized him and stabbed him.

45:17.000 --> 45:22.000
Then we realized that our cook was Merlin in disguise.

45:22.000 --> 45:29.000
Merlin did some terrible magic and now the boss is sleeping.

45:29.000 --> 45:34.000
He will never wake again.

45:34.000 --> 45:38.000
A final postscript by Mark Twain.

45:38.000 --> 45:41.000
At dawn, I stopped reading.

45:41.000 --> 45:45.000
I went to the stranger's room and knocked on the door.

45:45.000 --> 45:48.000
There was no answer.

45:48.000 --> 45:51.000
He was delirious.

45:51.000 --> 45:53.000
He spoke.

45:53.000 --> 45:57.000
Sandy, is that you?

45:57.000 --> 46:02.000
At last, now I can go back to you and our daughter.

46:02.000 --> 46:06.000
It was terrible without you.

46:06.000 --> 46:10.000
I am in the wrong century.

46:10.000 --> 46:12.000
A trumpet.

46:12.000 --> 46:16.000
It is the king.

46:16.000 --> 46:21.000
He never finished his sentence.

